The god of satire, jest, and biting truths. Folion embodies the spirit of the eternal jester.

He roams the realms of gods and mortals alike, draped in a cloak of vibrant patches, each representing a truth revealed through jest. His power lies in his ability to reveal harsh truths and critique societal norms under the guise of humor. Folion's laughter can either enlighten or sting, depending on the ears that hear it. With a mere jest, he can unveil the absurdity of political machinations, the folly of pride, and the irony of human endeavors, all while leaving his audience both amused and oftentimes, enlightened.